<br>
One of the magician's main gripes abour raids is being a candy-cane vending machine.<br>
<br>
Would wizards really object of Magician fire pets were given access to the Level 44 Wizard spell: Enticement of Flame?<br>
<br>
Level 52 fire pets are level 45 max, level 58s are 48 max. The level differential means that most spells are at least partially resisted, the addition of Enticement of Flame would make the pet much more desirable in raids.<br>
<br>
If this was implimented, would wizards really get all cranky and upset? Baring in mind that these pets are manna dependant and CAN run out!<br>
<br>
And, on a final note, let's keep the maturity level higher than the Jerry Springer show, please! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujarnin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jarnin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 2201<br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/3/02 11:52 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Magician Fire Pets: Imbicilic Wizards</span><hr size=1> I can officially say that I could give a rats ass if a magicians level 52+ fire pet casted enticement of flames. <p><CENTER>
